      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JOCK (1) was prominent throughout when winning two back but could manage only midfield last time when 5th and beaten 4.5 lengths at this track (25.18). Reliable out of the boxes and should take advantage of the inside draw. Can atone. ARMATREE VIOLET (5) goes very well this trip starting 33 times for 11 wins and nine minors. Below best last time at this track (25.13) in a Grade 3/4, finishing a 4 length fourth. Can hit the frame with the right run. RED ROCK RATTLER (4) boasts a consistent overall record including 12 wins from 45 starts, the latest hitting the minor money when second (18.48) over 318m at Dubbo. Goes well from this draw. Super consistent and can feature with the right run. SHE'S TIP TOP (7) is worth another chance despite missing the top-three here most recently.",
